U.S.: Repeat is the Mother of Wisdom
It’s funny that Barack Obama, the president with the reputation of the smartest man, as a diligent student repeats in the Afghan question the strategy of his predecessor, which he himself considered the dumbest.
When he finally revealed his anxious Afghan approach, it was shown to be a copy of the script used for Iraq by Bush, created three years ago.
Not only is the same text used several times the phrase "equal to Iraq", but it also did not hesitate to use the title of Bush's January 2007 statement for his own statement: "A new way forward."
It was he himself, who three years ago criticized Bush’s idea of sending new military reinforcements to Iraq, the country that is suffering from the civil war, and that criticized it as “an irresponsible decision with catastrophic consequences.”
The following months, however, proved that Bush’s strategy, based on the recommendations of the field captains, was the only possible and successful, so that today nothing about Iraq is spoken of in the news.
Bush’s reputation did not improve, but objectively left his successor a much more favourable initial situation than expected.
In Afghanistan, Barack Obama hopes the miracle will be repeated.
The field captains once again asked him to increase the military contingent, especially commander-in-chief of the Afghan General Operation Stanley McCristal. He, despite traditional subordinate relations, subjected the indecisive gunmen in the White House to harsh criticism.
He asked 40,000 men to improve the situation.
The president vacillated for three months, but nothing better happened to him, so at least he fooled the general over 10,000 soldiers.
He managed to get Europe to promise him another 5,000, although he himself had at least 10,000 before.
The most problematic of all Obama’s strategy seems to be his goal, to start withdrawing troops from Afghanistan in 18 months and finish this procedure in three years.
Many doubt that the increase will bear the same fruit as the procedure in Iraq.
Despite the fratricidal wars in recent years, Iraq’s society is relatively well organized, its leaders respect the agreements.
The situation in Afghanistan is different: it is not possible to trust anyone and no agreement is fulfilled.
Under these conditions, it is difficult to prepare Afghan security forces, if they are used to changing the head every day according to their needs.
The political institutions, although formally established, will remain only a Potemkin people, after which patriarchal tribal relations will remain.
Balance the interests of different ethnic groups is extraordinarily complicated due to confusing relations, even more complicated by Pakistani and Iranian influences.
Not even establishing a state that is "capable of action", a minimum goal of the whole operation, seems very real.
The horizon of Obama’s strategy is shocked by his volunteerism.
For the past eight years, the situation in Afghanistan has continued to deteriorate and is now about to erupt.
Only a romantic soul, who knows nothing about reality, can believe that the military sent to war to "return home soon", will do some miracle here.
From a political point of view, fixing the date of the withdrawal of troops is pure irresponsibility, as the Taliban will consider it an indirect declaration of American defeat.
The latest NATO summit showed that Europeans are less and less willing to participate in military operations in Afghanistan.
European politicians do not know, nor do they want to explain to their voters, what the security of Germany or Italy has to do with the war with the Hindu Kush.
The other factor, capable of radically affecting the situation, is the development of events in Iran.
If the situation continues to deteriorate and the increased sanctions do not have any effect on the Iranians, the U.S. will have to make a difficult decision: try to resolve the problem with military force or not.
It will be necessary to look for answers precisely when, according to Obama, America begins the triumphant withdrawal of Afghan troops.
However, each such solution will mean a dramatic reversal to the Afghan situation.
The only positive point for Barack Obama is the fact that there are three years left for the presidential election and that’s why there’s still a lot of time left to find another strategy, if it turns out to be a total failure.
