The CNMV has specified that the offer is aimed at the acquisition of 550,008 shares of Federico Paterina at a price of 7.65 euros per share, representing 8.95% of its share capital, which is composed of 6,142,786 shares admitted to trading on the Madrid and Bilbao Stock Exchanges.
It has also explained that 5,592,778 million shares have been immobilized, which will not be transmitted in any way until the end of the offer, of which it has specified that the price has been set by Federico Paterina, in accordance with the provisions of the current regulations.
New Tools to Peripheral Cars
In these days of accidents and accidents, not only car workshops win.
Every day thousands of cars that have suffered an accident are towed to a workshop, where an expert must assess the damage suffered and what will be the cost of repair.
No sinister is the same, and calculating the cost of parts and working time can be a long and complicated task.
Calculating the cost of a repair of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros, including parts and workmanship, can take two or three hours.
Instead, with the support of the latest computer tools, it would be a minor issue.
That’s why almost 100% of experts use this type of system.
Service providers and solutions for accident assessment and maintenance are dedicated to collecting the information that manufacturers provide them, then elaborate it and offer it to their customers in the form of a useful tool.
In Spain, Audatex, of the American group Solera, is the leading firm; 80% of the ratings are made with its products.
The other firms competing in the field of assessment and information processing tools on the sector are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data supplied by manufacturers is far from simple.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, commercial director of Audatex, in Spain they work with 63 manufacturers and importers, and each of them provides them with the information in different formats.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed continues to increase, to the point that in the last five years more versions, variants and engines have been released than in the previous fifteen.
As soon as a new car enters the market, these companies start working.
It is a very difficult task, because you have to catalog each of the thousands of parts of the vehicle and introduce its price.
In addition, of each model a "smart" graphic image is made where different parts of tourism can be "pinned".
If it is a ventamass model, the work can be ready in a week if the process goes very fast.
If you are a minority car, it can take three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information about 99.2% of cars sold in Spain.
Among the most exclusive models there are information about Porsche, but not from Ferrari or Lamborghini, for example.
As for the mobile park it circulates, it exceeds 99%.
To carry out the work of documentation and database development, Audatex has eight centers worldwide (Spain, France, Germany, USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan), and each of them is specialized in specific brands.
