Workshop budget in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audatex ensures that the user gets a budget in just four steps: identifying the vehicle, looking for the spare parts, creating a budget and generating a budget.
Ease of use is an essential conditioner for these systems, especially to convince older professionals that to a greater or lesser extent they are more reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, which are 666 cars, 109 all-terrain, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, to use it you need a computer with an internet connection.
Once the model to be repaired by its frame number is identified, a real graphic image of the model in question is displayed and then the necessary replacement is selected.
The user can include variables such as labor price, charges or discounts, and then can print the budget to deliver to the customer.
AudaTaller is not a rating tool like AudaPlus, but rather a catalog of references.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool for the workshop is 350 euros per year, which the customer can finance.
